reviews.subject: Computer Science
reviews.review: Dr. Smith is an excellent professor who explains complex algorithms in a simple way. His lectures are always engaging.

reviews.subject: Mathematics
reviews.review: Prof. Johnson is very knowledgeable, but her lectures can be hard to follow sometimes. She expects a lot from her students.

reviews.subject: Data Structures
reviews.review: Dr. Williams is a decent professor, but his exams are extremely difficult. The homework assignments are helpful, though.

reviews.subject: History
reviews.review: Prof. Brown is very passionate about history. She brings the subject to life with her stories and examples. Highly recommend her class!

reviews.subject: Chemistry
reviews.review: Dr. Davis is a tough grader, but his lectures are clear and well-organized. You'll learn a lot if you put in the effort.

reviews.subject: Literature
reviews.review: Prof. Wilson's classes are interesting, but she can be a bit strict with deadlines. She provides great feedback on essays.

reviews.subject: Philosophy
reviews.review: Dr. Martinez is a brilliant thinker, but his lectures can be confusing. The readings are heavy, but worth it.

reviews.subject: Economics
reviews.review: Prof. Lee is an amazing professor who makes economics fun. Her exams are fair, and she is always willing to help students outside of class.

reviews.subject: Biology
reviews.review: Dr. Garcia is very enthusiastic about biology, but his lectures can be a bit dry. He is approachable and helps students understand difficult concepts.

reviews.subject: Political Science
reviews.review: Prof. Thompson is very knowledgeable, but she can be hard to approach. Her lectures are informative, but not very engaging.

reviews.subject: Artificial Intelligence
reviews.review: Dr. Adams is a genius in AI, but his lectures can be overwhelming. You need to stay on top of the material.

reviews.subject: Software Engineering
reviews.review: Prof. Evans is amazing at breaking down complex software development processes. Her assignments are challenging but rewarding.

reviews.subject: Machine Learning
reviews.review: Dr. Wilson’s course is intense, but you will learn a lot about machine learning. Be prepared for heavy coding assignments.

reviews.subject: Human-Computer Interaction
reviews.review: Prof. Scott is very passionate about HCI. Her projects are hands-on and fun, and she encourages creativity.

reviews.subject: Computer Networks
reviews.review: Dr. Young is knowledgeable but expects students to be self-motivated. His exams are tough, but he prepares you well.

reviews.subject: Operating Systems
reviews.review: Prof. Clark’s class is challenging, especially the coding assignments, but she’s very supportive and provides great feedback.

reviews.subject: Database Systems
reviews.review: Dr. White is an excellent professor with a deep understanding of databases. His lectures are clear and well-structured.

reviews.subject: Cybersecurity
reviews.review: Prof. Baker makes cybersecurity topics interesting. Her labs are practical and help reinforce the concepts taught in class.

reviews.subject: Algorithms
reviews.review: Dr. Green is a tough professor, but you’ll gain a strong foundation in algorithms. His problem sets are hard but rewarding.

reviews.subject: Data Science
reviews.review: Prof. Hill is very approachable and helpful. Her assignments are practical, focusing on real-world data science problems.
